OL,3,CD-Day veteran awarded British Empire
OL,4,CMedal says Britain today is
OL,5,C'disappointing'
OL,7,FA D-Day veteran awarded a British
OL,8,FEmpire Medal has said Britain today is
OL,9,F"disappointing" and warned the country
OL,10,Frisks repeating mistakes made before
OL,11,Fthe Second World War.
OL,13,FMervyn Kersh, 101, from Cockfosters,
OL,14,Fnorth London, said being honoured for
OL,15,Fhis school talks on Holocaust
OL,16,Fremembrance and his wartime service is
OL,17,Fa "wonderful thing".
