OL,7,FMr Kersh likened the honour to being
OL,8,Fawarded the Legion d'honneur `
OL,9,FFrance's highest military award ` but
OL,10,Fsaid it was significant to be
OL,11,Frecognised by his own country.
OL,13,FHe told the Press Association that
OL,14,Fefforts to speak about the Holocaust
OL,15,F"not always work", telling of his
OL,16,Fconcerns about rising antisemitism in
OL,17,Fthe UK.
