OL,3,CD-Day veteran awarded British Empire
OL,4,CMedal says Britain today is
OL,5,C'disappointing'
OL,7,FMr Kersh said he believes his service
OL,8,Fduring the Second World War "was worth
OL,9,Fit", but added: "It's disappointing
OL,10,Fwhat's turned out now."
OL,12,FHe went on: "What's disappointing is
OL,13,Fthe antisemitism that I see
OL,14,Feverywhere, hear everywhere, or read."
OL,16,FMr Kersh arrived in Normandy aged 19,
OL,17,Fthree days after the start of the D-
OL,18,FDay invasion in June 1944, serving as
OL,19,Fa technical clerk for the Royal Army
OL,20,FOrdnance Corps, organising vehicle
OL,21,Fsupport.
